You've heard about the Protein Princesses - women working out 
multiple times per week - but there's a new breed of gym bunnies giving the likes of fitness fanatic Millie Mackintosh a run for her money.

Middle-aged men are forging a new unofficial cult of gym-goers being dubbed MAMILs (middle aged men in lycra), who are becoming obsessed with going to the gym to bulk up.

This breed of over 40s now represent more than one in ten of the nation’s bodybuilders and they're inspired by muscular role models 
including Hugh Jackman, 45, Gerard Butler, 44, and current ‘Hercules’ actor, 42-year-old
Dwayne ‘The Rock’ Johnson.

