Patrick Dempsey, 47, is also an avid gym goer and lifts weights every week, as well as cycling most places.

He's frequently spotted riding, and told Men's Health that he likes to get in about 100 miles a week.

A spokesperson for Bodybuilding Warehouse, who commissioned the survey, said: 'It’s great to see that men aged 40 and above are not viewing their age as an excuse to slow down, but as an extra motivation to look after their fitness and overall well-being.

'Working out four times a week or more is an excellent way to maintain health, prevent middle age spread and maintain a positive mental attitude.'

